1
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:40,999
All right then.

2
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:44,669
Let's find out more about literary trends.

3
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:47,839
-The trend of literature...
-It was love.

4
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,968
A literary trend
has two general definitions.

5
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:56,723
One is the change of thought
behind literary arts throughout history.

6
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,308
And the other

7
00:00:58,391 --> 00:01:02,353
has more to do with the means
of expression in literary arts.

8
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:23,792
That's it for today.

9
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,044
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

10
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,266
-Let's go to eat.
-I'm on a diet.

11
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:46,940
Do you want to eat with me?

12
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:49,567
Pardon? I mean...

13
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:51,653
Me?

14
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:53,988
My friend who usually eats with me
didn't come today.

15
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,281
Let's go.

16
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:57,826
Okay.

17
00:01:58,284 --> 00:01:59,369
What do you like?

18
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:01,996
Tteokbokki?

19
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:14,342
-I guess you like spicy food.
-What?

20
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,470
Well... I do.

21
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:18,888
-Wheat tteok?
-Yes.

22
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,557
With plenty of soup in it.

23
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,934
Right. I like to mash
the egg yolk in the soup.

24
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,561
And it should have
artificial flavors in it.

25
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:26,855
With some pickled radish.

26
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,905
I was going to eat alone.

27
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:37,699
Me too.

28
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,033
Don't you have friends?

29
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:40,702
I don't have a lot.

30
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,830
But in a few years,

31
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,206
I think

32
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:48,042
eating and drinking alone
could become a new trend.

33
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:50,378
What kind of trend is that?

34
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:52,672
Then you mean
there will be restaurants or bars

35
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:53,923
where people eat and drink alone?

36
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:55,717
That sounds a little strange.

37
00:02:56,175 --> 00:02:59,762
Maybe not a trend,
but it will be something we find familiar.

38
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,599
-It sounds heartless.
-I know.

39
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,684
I guess you're right.

40
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,647
Thank you for asking me to eat with you.

41
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,943
I wanted to eat with you.

42
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:18,907
I see.

43
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,745
Can I ask you why?

44
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:26,706
-Why did you quit the club?
-What?

45
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:29,000
-Because I did first.
-Right.

46
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,627
Why did you change
your liberal arts class?

47
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,338
You did it to see me.

48
00:03:44,891 --> 00:03:45,725
Soju?

49
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:48,311
That's what I've been drinking.

50
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,397
I guess you like bitter stuff.

51
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:53,149
Yes, I do.

52
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:55,276
Something bitter in broad daylight?

53
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,070
I didn't think
I could pluck up my courage.

54
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:03,910
Now that I did something,
it's your turn to make a move.

55
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:08,748
How much soju gets you tipsy?

56
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:10,458
Half a bottle?

57
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:13,086
Drink it a little more.

58
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:28,393
All right.

59
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:30,478
Now you can tell me what you want to say.

60
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,616
I like you.

61
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,244
DAY 1 OF THEIR RELATIONSHIP

62
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:47,620
In fact,

63
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:51,124
tteokbokki is more sweet than spicy.

64
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:53,793
And soju is not bitter but sweet.

65
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:57,755
But I don't think that's the reason

66
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,091
why our kiss was so sweet.

67
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:02,135
It was love.

68
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:08,308
Do you know

69
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:11,019
what a woman's eyes look like
when she is in love with a man?

70
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:12,562
What do they look like?

71
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:22,530
Do you know what a man's nose looks like
when he is in love with a woman?

72
00:05:22,613 --> 00:05:23,740
What does it look like?

73
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:30,496
Don't do that.

74
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:33,541
DAY 50

75
00:05:33,624 --> 00:05:36,461
Countless words that we exchanged

76
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:40,381
were just some silly words
that were randomly put together,

77
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,759
but they were
the sweetest whispers in the world.

78
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:46,721
FORGIVENESS COUPON

79
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:51,893
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

80
00:05:54,645 --> 00:05:57,690
And we were given justification
for all our behaviors

81
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:00,902
that were just childish and immature.

82
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:14,082
-Did you enjoy your class?
-Yes.

83
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:18,795
I'll go throw up.

84
00:06:19,962 --> 00:06:21,130
I'll come with you.

85
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:25,551
It was only the witnesses
who felt uncomfortable.

86
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:27,970
We were always like that.

87
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:31,099
And over time,
"always" became "once in a while."

88
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,100
I said sorry!

89
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:34,060
-Forget it.
-It happened once in a while.

90
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:35,103
Hey.

91
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:36,896
-Get off me.
-And we fought once in a while, too.

92
00:06:36,979 --> 00:06:38,481
-Let go of me.
-I said I'm sorry.

93
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,566
I said let go. Get off me!

94
00:06:42,276 --> 00:06:43,361
Okay.

95
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:49,450
FORGIVENESS COUPON

96
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:13,182
DAY 300

97
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:16,227
One day, we implicitly came to believe

98
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,980
that fights wouldn't lead to a breakup.

99
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,859
The belief put us at ease.

100
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:27,280
And, ironically, being at ease made us
not tolerate each other's differences

101
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:29,949
like we used to do in the beginning.

102
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,494
That's how our fights repeated

103
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,580
and got fierce.

104
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:37,790
No,

105
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,584
it became pathetic.

106
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,061
What do you want to say?
Why are you frowning again?

107
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,773
You don't know what I was about to say.
Why are you throwing tantrums?

108
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:05,151
I just held your hand.
I didn't throw tantrums.

109
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:06,819
I held your hand first.

110
00:08:06,903 --> 00:08:08,279
You never apologize first.

111
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:11,782
Does it really matter who did wrong
and who apologized first?

112
00:08:11,866 --> 00:08:13,576
Why don't you study statistics?

113
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,578
You didn't even text me
when you got home on Friday.

114
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:16,579
Why did you not text me?

115
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,331
Why would you bring that up?

116
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:20,833
I was saying you throw tantrums
and never apologize.

117
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:23,002
We should finish talking about your flaws

118
00:08:23,085 --> 00:08:25,087
before moving on to talking about mine.

119
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:27,215
When I didn't apologize,
I was too tired to do so.

120
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:29,967
You were the one
who freaked out and criticized me.

121
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:32,053
I was like that only once.

122
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:34,347
I said we should finish
talking about your flaws first.

123
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:37,767
You drank until late at night
and didn't answer my calls

124
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,352
until the next afternoon.

125
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:40,895
Did you not hear me?

126
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,730
Finish talking about yourself first.

127
00:08:42,813 --> 00:08:44,524
Why does it even matter?

128
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,150
Of course it matters.

129
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,027
Do you really have to say that
holding my hand?

130
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,153
Let go of it then.

131
00:08:50,112 --> 00:08:51,781
Don't you dare leave. Then we're over.

132
00:08:57,078 --> 00:09:00,790
DAY 500

133
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,267
Hey!

134
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:21,769
It's raining.

135
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:43,165
DAY 800

136
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,672
It was a wound that required a bandage

137
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:52,091
but we tried to seal it
with a small Band-Aid.

138
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:56,554
Can we stop walking?

139
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:59,265
We should have a walk
when there's no fine dust.

140
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:02,893
You could've just said so.
What are you so annoyed about?

141
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:05,062
I wasn't annoyed, I was just saying.

142
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:07,231
Then why are you frowning?

143
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:10,776
Do you think I can't tell
whether you're annoyed or not?

144
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:12,111
What's your problem?

145
00:10:12,194 --> 00:10:14,572
I told you. I want to stop walking.

146
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:16,365
So you do have a problem.

147
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,576
You were annoyed.

148
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:20,620
You weren't just saying it.

149
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:23,789
Do you want me to admit
that I threw a tantrum?

150
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,666
Is it what you want right now?

151
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:29,670
You are always like that. What's
your problem? Does it run in your blood?

152
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:30,755
Run in my blood?

153
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:33,257
Are you petty
because it runs in your blood?

154
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:35,259
Petty?

155
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:37,970
Then you shouldn't see me.

156
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:40,222
-Did you say you want to break up with me?
-You said that.

157
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:42,516
No. Just say it.
You want to break up with me, right?

158
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:45,436
-You tell me. You want to break up.
-You say it.

159
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:47,480
Okay. Let's break up. Let's just do it.

160
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:50,274
-You want to break up with me?
-Yes. Did you not get it?

161
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:52,318
Don't you understand Korean?
Shall I speak in English?

162
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:53,819
Go ahead and say it in English.

163
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:57,365
Get lost!

164
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:01,535
What? Thank you? Hey.

165
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:04,914
"Thank you?" Say that again.
Are you thankful?

166
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,585
Say that again. "Thank you?"
Is that what you're supposed to say?

167
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,921
Why? I can't say that when you can?

168
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:14,590
That's what you said to me
last time we broke up.

169
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,062
A FEW DAYS AFTER DAY 900

170
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,313
We struggled.

171
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:31,524
We struggled to hold back,

172
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:35,653
breaking up and getting back together
over and over again for no reason.

173
00:11:36,278 --> 00:11:38,989
And we got the hang of breaking up
with only one word.

174
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:40,908
DONE

175
00:11:40,991 --> 00:11:42,284
DONE

176
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:44,703
DONE

177
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:46,831
HEY

178
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:50,584
HEY

179
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,211
WHAT

180
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:54,672
And we also learned to get back together

181
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:56,674
with only one word, too.

182
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,117
By the time we started to see

183
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,911
restaurants and bars
where people eat and drink alone,

184
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:30,708
we finally broke up for real.

185
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:36,046
Two nights ago,

186
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:39,675
my friend saw you...

187
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:41,969
at a motel.

188
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:47,183
Do you have anything to say?

189
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:53,856
I believed it wasn't love

190
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:57,860
when we broke up
slashing at each other's heart,

191
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:00,613
even when it seemed like
they wouldn't be wounded anymore.

192
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:04,867
I believed it wasn't love
after we had become numb over time.

193
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:07,536
But it turns out what I wanted to believe

194
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:11,207
was a persistent lie
that I hid deep down in my heart.

195
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,584
Love may change,

196
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,878
but the truth doesn't.

197
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:18,214
It was love.

198
00:13:19,256 --> 00:13:22,301
But the reason I cried yesterday...

199
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:24,595
It's not because I'm not over him.

200
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,847
It's that I can't forget my heartaches.

201
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:30,518
It means I'm not over myself, not him.

202
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:33,938
I spent most of my 20s with only one man.

203
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:36,565
It just made me feel sad.

204
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:37,942
That's it.

205
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:42,738
Come to think of it, you spent the time
when you were prettiest on the outside

206
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:45,074
with Hwan-dong who was at his lowest.

207
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:47,535
What? Now is the time when I'm prettiest.

208
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:50,829
What makes you think that?

209
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:53,165
My mental attitude.

210
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:57,127
-She needs to be compensated.
-Compensated?

211
00:13:57,711 --> 00:14:00,839
She felt happy anyway
during that time, didn't she?

212
00:14:01,549 --> 00:14:03,551
I don't think it's something
that requires compensation.

213
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,804
And it's not like women are the only ones
who are prettiest in their 20s.

214
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:09,932
Don't you think it was the same
for Hwan-dong as well?

215
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:12,643
Well... I guess he'd feel that way
if he was gay.

216
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:16,313
I mean, he must be a precious son
to his family anyway.

217
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,274
You're usually on our side,

218
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:20,860
but you change your position
when we speak ill of a cute guy.

219
00:14:21,068 --> 00:14:22,778
Does Mun-su know that you're like this?

220
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,989
Yes. That's why he likes me.

221
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:29,243
Fine. Let's say it isn't something
that requires compensation.

222
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:33,330
But I'd like to question
the barbaric perspective

223
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:36,375
of believing that the value of women

224
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:38,627
-depends on their appearance.
-All of a sudden?

225
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:42,840
Men should never be with beautiful women
if they approach them with such beliefs.

226
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:44,967
We, who are beautiful on the outside,

227
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,928
should teach them that. Get ready.

228
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,307
What? Get ready for what?

229
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,559
I think we are going to a club.

230
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,562
Look after In-guk for me.

231
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,480
I can't believe them.

232
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,901
Why would they go to a club
after talking about their past love?

233
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:04,778
It was all planned out, right?

234
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:09,658
Are you guys kidding me?

235
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:06,715
Eun-jeong.

236
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:09,927
Why aren't guys chatting us up?

237
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:13,889
I don't know. Are we supposed
to sign up for something?

238
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,408
-That's enough.
-Get off me.

239
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:34,493
-Let's talk outside.
-I told you to let go of me.

240
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,799
The fish bit at the bait.
My external beauty is

241
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:51,969
just irresistible to those ignorant fish.

242
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,762
I'm a true fisherwoman in a city.

243
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:54,847
What are you doing?

244
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:57,683
What am I supposed to say

245
00:16:57,766 --> 00:17:01,687
if he asks me what I'm doing
when I'm dancing?

246
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:04,690
Deviation.

247
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,703
Who are you here with?

248
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,663
My boyfriend.

249
00:17:33,635 --> 00:17:35,971
You're pretty. Can I join you?

250
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:38,932
I have a kid.

251
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:41,518
I see. Good for you.

252
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:02,831
What?

253
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,210
Why is this so good?
I thought 24-hour joints sucked.

254
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:09,880
I know. We just found a good restaurant.

255
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:13,008
It feels like we're out to eat this.

256
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,428
Shall we order some suyuk too?

257
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:18,972
Sure.

258
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:23,727
-One suyuk please.
-Okay.

259
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,148
Can I eat now?

260
00:18:29,066 --> 00:18:30,442
-Are you done?
